# v50/v51 Browser Evaluation — Cursor rule

Source of Truth: `AGENTS.md` `## Browser Evaluation / Scoring Delivery SoT`.

- Browser evaluation must not call Gmail.
- Keep scoring core separated from delivery.
- Preserve legacy ElevenLabs post-call Gmail path unless explicitly changing it.
- The shared Adecco scoring prompt/schema bundle currently defaults to customer
  criteria v2 and affects v51 browser evaluation, v50-7 browser evaluation, and
  legacy Gmail scoring unless an explicit evaluation profile split is added.
- Versioned browser evaluation routes should use `session.browserEvaluation` for
  start endpoint, result base path, and source.
- Result APIs must not expose raw Claude output, secrets, relay tickets, prompt
  instructions, or raw audio.
- Cloud Tasks payload may include only the normalized evaluation transcript
  required for scoring.
- Use the mock result route before production checks. For v51/customer criteria
  work, use `/demo/adecco-roleplay-v51/result/mock-session?mock=1`.
- Do not run production Gmail smoke unless explicitly requested.
